      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "An issue I could imagine with \"testing recommendations\" is that they are done sporadically or not all all, because no one wants to spend time going through a long document with bullet points and check them off before every release.\r\n\r\nObviously we have the unit and functional tests, which is our primary point to put new tests in. Everyone should run them after compiling Bitcoin Core. For the gitian builds, I do this on all platforms: mac, win, linux.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to user testing, every user has their own use case for Bitcoin Core, so beside running the unit and functional tests, they should read the release notes and run their own integration tests (e.g. \"Is my RPC wrapper still up to date with the all RPC changes\") every time they update Bitcoin Core.",
      "user": {
        "login": "MarcoFalke",
        "id": 6399679,
        "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYzOTk2Nzk=",
